## Output Format -- STRICT

You MUST respond with a single JSON object that conforms exactly to the
`analysis_output` schema in Section 5 of the system prompt above.

- Output ONLY the JSON object. Do not wrap it in markdown fences. Do not
  prepend or append commentary, explanations, or chain-of-thought.
- All field names must match the schema exactly (snake_case).
- Enum-valued fields must use one of the documented literal strings
  (e.g. `problem_type` is one of `"diagnostic"`, `"design"`,
  `"evaluation"`, `"prediction"`).
- `key_arguments` must contain at least one entry; the schema rejects an
  empty list.
- `issue_tree.branches` must contain at least one entry.
- `governing_thought.statement` must be a complete sentence (the
  elevator-test sentence), not a topic label.
- `validation_log` should record the eight self-validation checks; for
  this pass, set `result` to `"not_applicable"` for any check the agent
  cannot perform on its own and explain why in `details`.
- Every `evidence` item's `assigned_to` MUST equal a `key_arguments[].id`
  and its `branch_id` MUST equal a `issue_tree.branches[...].id` (or a
  recursively nested sub-branch id).

The user's problem statement follows.
